The article discusses a mass shooting that took place in Allen, Texas, expressing condolences for the victims and gratitude towards the first responders. It emphasizes the need for gun violence prevention measures and highlights that a majority of Americans, including gun owners, support sensible reforms. The article mentions that President Biden has already signed significant gun safety legislation and implemented executive actions, but more action is needed. The article calls for a bill to be sent to President Biden that bans assault weapons and high-capacity magazines, implements universal background checks, and helps prevent guns from falling into the wrong hands.